FBIS3-5786 "dreas047bb_94002" FBIS-EAS-94-047 Document Type:Daily Report 10 Mar 1994 INTER-ASIAN AFFAIRS Openness Toward Newly Liberalized Nations Urged BK0903080294 Quezon City Radio Filipinas in English 0230 GMT 9 Mar 94 BK0903080294 Quezon City Radio Filipinas Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] The Philippines has asked the Association of Southeast Nations, or ASEAN, to adopt a more open attitude toward newly liberalized countries in the region. These countries are Cambodia, Laos, Myanmar [Burma], and Vietnam. The call was made by the Philippine delegation to the special meeting of the ASEAN senior officials held recently in Bangkok. Delegation head Foreign Affairs Undersecretary Rodolfo Severino called on ASEAN to eventually accept these newly industrialized [as heard] countries into the association. He said the inclusion of these four countries in ASEAN could prevent future conflicts and promote political stability and economic progress.
